---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PostCard from '../components/PostCard.astro';
import { getBlogPosts } from '../utils/getPosts';

const allBlog = await getBlogPosts();
// Pull posts whose category is in the Kingdom Farm / Faith family —
// matches the same buckets used by the home-page "Farm Vision" column.
const farmPosts = allBlog
	.filter((p) => ['Kingdom Farm', 'Faith', 'Faith & Reflections'].includes(p.data.category))
	.slice(0, 4);
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Kingdom Farm"
	description="Regenerative farming for food independence. Clean food shouldn’t be a privilege."
>
	<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 md:py-24">
		<!-- Hero -->
		<div class="mb-16 text-center md:mb-20">
			<div
				class="bg-primary/10 text-primary mb-6 inline-flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl"
			>
				<svg
					xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
					class="h-8 w-8"
					viewBox="0 0 20 20"
					fill="currentColor"
				>
					<path
						fill-rule="evenodd"
						d="M4 2a2 2 0 00-2 2v11a3 3 0 106 0V4a2 2 0 00-2-2H4zm1 14a1 1 0 100-2 1 1 0 000 2zm5-1.757l4.9-4.9a2 2 0 000-2.828L13.485 5.1a2 2 0 00-2.828 0L10 5.757v8.486zM16 18H9.071l6-6H16a2 2 0 012 2v2a2 2 0 01-2 2z"
						clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
				</svg>
			</div>
			<h1 class="font-display mb-4 text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight md:text-6xl">
				Kingdom Farm
			</h1>
			<p class="text-base-content/70 mx-auto max-w-2xl text-2xl leading-tight md:text-3xl">
				Regenerative farming for food independence.<br class="hidden md:block" />
				Clean food shouldn’t be a privilege.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- The Vision -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>The vision</h2>
			<p>
				We’re a family of six building a regenerative farm — not as a hobby, but as a response to a
				problem we live every month: paying $2,000–$3,000 just to feed our kids clean, nutritious
				food. That’s rent money in most places. Most families can’t do it.
			</p>
			<p>
				We’re studying pasture-based, regenerative models popularized by farmers like Joel Salatin —
				rotational grazing, healthy soil, animals raised with respect, and direct-to-family food
				systems. Our plan is to run an ad-hoc CSA with simple recipes so families who can’t normally
				afford organic can eat well. Long-term, we hope to help encourage and equip other small
				farmers so more communities can move toward real food independence.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Why This Matters -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>Why this matters</h2>
			<p>
				Clean, nutritious food should not be a privilege. It should be normal. When families can’t
				afford it, their health, energy, and future pay the price. We’ve felt that strain ourselves.
			</p>
			<p>
				We believe a well-run regenerative farm can do more than grow food. It can grow hope. It can
				restore dignity. It can show people that someone cares about their bodies and their tables —
				not just their wallets.
			</p>
			<p class="font-medium">
				That’s the kind of place we want to build. One that feels like Jesus loving people on earth
				through dirt, sweat, and good food.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- What We Hope to Build -->
		<div class="mb-16">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-6 text-3xl font-bold">What we hope to build</h2>

			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">A regenerative farm</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						Pasture-based systems that build soil, produce real food, and treat animals and land
						with dignity.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">An ad-hoc CSA with recipes</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						Weekly or bi-weekly shares for families who want clean food but can’t normally afford it
						— plus simple, practical recipes so the food actually gets used and enjoyed.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Seeding other farmers (long-term)</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						We hope to help encourage and equip other small farmers so more communities can move
						toward real food independence.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Where We Are Right Now -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>Where we are right now</h2>
			<p>
				We’ve been full-time RVing with our four kids (ages 4, 7, 10, and 12) for over two and a
				half years. I work full-time as a senior software engineer. We’re currently traveling in the
				RV while scouting land in and around the Floyd County area of Georgia.
			</p>
			<p>
				We don’t have the farm yet. We have a clear direction, a growing conviction, and a
				willingness to do the slow, honest work of figuring this out in public. We’re sharing as
				much as we can honestly and wisely.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- What This Is Not (NEW) -->
		<div class="bg-base-200 mb-16 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-10">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-6 text-center text-2xl font-bold">What this is not</h2>

			<div class="text-base-content/80 mx-auto max-w-md space-y-4">
				<p><strong>Kingdom Farm is not</strong> a polished success story yet.</p>
				<p><strong>It is not</strong> a fundraiser disguised as a blog.</p>
				<p><strong>It is not</strong> a promise that we have all the answers.</p>

				<p class="text-base-content pt-2 font-medium">
					It is a family learning in public, counting the cost, and trying to build something useful
					and faithful.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- What We’re Learning -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>What we’re learning along the way</h2>
			<p>
				Every month we’re learning about soil, grazing, costs, business models, and what it actually
				takes to make this kind of food accessible instead of elite. We’re also learning about
				ourselves — what we’re willing to give up, what we’re not, and how to keep hope alive when
				progress feels slow.
			</p>
			<p class="font-medium">This isn’t a highlight reel. It’s the real, messy, hopeful path.</p>
		</div>

		<!-- How to Follow -->
		<div class="bg-base-200 mb-16 rounded-3xl p-10 text-center">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-4 text-3xl font-bold">How to follow the journey</h2>
			<p class="text-base-content/80 mx-auto mb-8 max-w-md">
				The best way to stay with us is through honest monthly updates — land search stories,
				research, cost breakdowns, lessons learned, and the quiet prayers that shape the vision.
			</p>

			<div class="mx-auto max-w-xs">
				<a href="/#newsletter" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg w-full">
					Follow the Kingdom Farm journey
				</a>
				<p class="text-base-content/60 mt-3 text-xs">Monthly updates • Real talk • No spam</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Ways to Help -->
		<div class="mb-16">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-4 text-center text-3xl font-bold">Ways to help right now</h2>
			<p class="text-base-content/70 mx-auto mb-8 max-w-md text-center">
				Not everyone can give money. That’s okay. Here’s what would actually move the mission
				forward today:
			</p>

			<div class="mx-auto grid max-w-2xl gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 font-semibold">Share the vision</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						If this mission resonates, tell people who care about food, farming, or helping
						families.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 font-semibold">Offer advice or expertise</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						We’re still learning. If you know regenerative farming, soil, business setup, or land in
						north Georgia — we’d love your input.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 font-semibold">Supplies or labor (later)</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						Once we have land, help with fencing, tools, or hands-on work will be huge.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 font-semibold">Pray with us</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						This is a faith-shaped mission. Your prayers matter more than you know.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Live posts pulled from the Kingdom Farm / Faith categories.
		     Mirrors the rv-life.astro pattern. -->
		{
			farmPosts.length > 0 ? (
				<div class="mb-16">
					<div class="mb-8 flex items-baseline gap-4">
						<span class="eyebrow">From the blog</span>
						<span class="border-base-content/15 flex-1 border-t" />
						<a
							href="/category/Kingdom%20Farm/"
							class="font-display text-base-content/60 hover:text-primary text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase transition-colors"
						>
							All Kingdom Farm posts →
						</a>
					</div>
					<div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
						{farmPosts.map((post) => (
							<PostCard kind="blog" entry={post} />
						))}
					</div>
				</div>
			) : (
				<div class="border-base-300 mb-16 rounded-2xl border p-8 text-center">
					<p class="font-display mb-2 text-lg font-bold">Kingdom Farm posts coming soon</p>
					<p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm">
						Land scouting, water planning, and the long-obedience updates. Subscribe to catch them
						when they land.
					</p>
				</div>
			)
		}

		<!-- Kingdom Farm Builders (Soft) -->
		<div class="border-t pt-12">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-xl text-center">
				<h2 class="font-display mb-4 text-3xl font-bold">Kingdom Farm Builders</h2>
				<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-6 text-lg">
					Some of you have asked how you can support the mission financially. We’re grateful.
				</p>
				<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-8">
					We’re not launching a formal support program yet. Right now the most important thing is
					building trust through honest updates and real progress. When the time comes, we’ll invite
					a small group of early Builders to help fund specific milestones — and we’ll be
					transparent about how every dollar is used. You’ll be the first to know.
				</p>

				<a href="/#newsletter" class="btn btn-outline"> Stay in the loop </a>

				<p class="text-base-content/60 mx-auto mt-8 max-w-sm text-xs">
					Kingdom Farm is a family mission in progress. We’re committed to being honest about where
					we are, where we’re going, and what it actually takes.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>
